  "description": "A group homomorphism is a [function](../../../concepts/function/index.md) $phi : G \to H$ between [groups](./group.md) that preserves the group operation: $phi(a cdot b) = phi(a) cdot phi(b)$ for all $a, b in G$. This extends the notion of [homomorphism](../../prealgebra/terms/homomorphism.md) from [monoids](../../prealgebra/terms/monoid.md) to groups.",
